"Drinking from the fountain of green and non-green energy" is a metaphorical way to describe the consumption of renewable and non-renewable energy; "last half-decade" refers to the last five years; "how plentiful their draught has been on average" means the average consumption/production levels.;

The metaphor "fountain of green and non-green energy" signifies the source or consumption of renewable (green) and non-renewable (non-green) energy resources. This is a figurative approach to discuss energy consumption trends over a specific period, focusing on sustainability and resource depletion concerns.;

"Last half-decade" is a poetic way of saying "last five years," emphasizing a recent and specific timeframe to examine trends.;

The term "draught" is used here metaphorically to indicate the amount of energy consumed or produced, suggesting how much each country has "drunk" from these energy sources. The average consumption/production levels provide a comparative measure of the sustainability and reliance on energy types across different countries.;

Energy consumption over a fixed period, such as five years, can be crucial for understanding trends and making projections for future energy needs and policies.;

sql:
SELECT year, SUM(total_energy) AS global_total_energy
FROM global_energy_data
GROUP BY year;

SELECT COUNT(*) as count_high_population_countries
FROM countries
WHERE population > (SELECT AVG(population) FROM countries);

SELECT entity, renewable_energy
FROM global_energy_data
WHERE renewable_energy = (SELECT MIN(renewable_energy) FROM global_energy_data);

SELECT storage_id, country_id, storage_type, capacity, utilization_rate
FROM energy_storage
WHERE country_id = 1 AND storage_type = 'battery';

SELECT AVG(total_consumption) 
FROM historical_energy_data
WHERE year BETWEEN 2010 AND 2020;
